abstract: An analysis of three years of Police Department data showed a broad decline in racially disparate policing, a significant change since the Bloomberg administration.
snippet: An analysis of three years of Police Department data showed a broad decline in racially disparate policing, a significant change since the Bloomberg administration.
lead_paragraph: Street stops by New York City police officers have plunged since 2011 and a new statistical analysis by a federal monitor concludes that the racial disparity in stops is narrowing.

abstract: Assemblywoman Nicole Malliotakis is positioning herself as an antithesis to Mayor Bill de Blasio, even as she tries to distance herself from President Trump.
snippet: Assemblywoman Nicole Malliotakis is positioning herself as an antithesis to Mayor Bill de Blasio, even as she tries to distance herself from President Trump.
lead_paragraph: As two would-be Republican challengers to Mayor Bill de Blasio of New York addressed dozens of Republican Party members and well-heeled donors at a political club in Midtown Manhattan, the specter of President Trump loomed large, in every sense.

abstract: His donation helps solidify New York’s first new cultural institution in recent memory, a $500 million project to be completed in spring 2019.
snippet: His donation helps solidify New York’s first new cultural institution in recent memory, a $500 million project to be completed in spring 2019.
lead_paragraph: The ambitious new arts center known as the Shed, rising in Hudson Yards, has received $75 million from Michael R. Bloomberg, showing just how much the Far West Side continues to be shaped by a small group of influential billionaires.

headline_main: Michael Bloomberg Gives $75 Million to Shed Arts Center

abstract: A driver’s rampage, then an attack in England lead to a re-examination of how to balance security and convenience in busy areas of Manhattan.
snippet: A driver’s rampage, then an attack in England lead to a re-examination of how to balance security and convenience in busy areas of Manhattan.
lead_paragraph: Planners describe it as a turning point in the redesign of Times Square: a meeting around the end of 2012 when David C. Kelly, then the Police Department’s assistant commissioner for counterterrorism, showed up with a copy of Al Qaeda’s English-language magazine, which called on attackers to "mow down” pedestrians with pickup trucks.

abstract: By placing college advisers in public schools, an organization is trying to break down the social, economic and psychological barriers that keep low-income rural students from dreaming big.
snippet: By placing college advisers in public schools, an organization is trying to break down the social, economic and psychological barriers that keep low-income rural students from dreaming big.
lead_paragraph: SAMPSON COUNTY, N.C. — The first time Nyreke Peters met the new college adviser at his rural high school, he was skeptical. Other adults at Hobbton High School spoke with the same Southern accent and shared an easygoing familiarity that came from having gone to the same schools and having spent their lives in the same county.
